ible” secretary sebelius said but she couldn’t give dr sanjay gupta a specific date “millions of americans want this product” she said which is no doubt a lot of people aren’t tech savvy with “lots of people” wanting a “live body” to talk to about signing up this “isn’t a website it’s about health care and about affordable plans” whether the individual mandate will be delayed is “not really the question right now” according to sebelius “you need everybody to come into the pool… we need people to sign up” secretary sebelius said at the end of the interview that she is looking to the enrollment figures at the end of march  when open enrollment ends it sounds like that’s when we’ll know the full numbers and success of the launch of aca right as the  midterms are gearing up i’m not sure anything kathleen sebelius says will change the dynamic right now but it’s an interview she had to do with more administration officials needed to continue making the case if people don’t have confidence not enough will sign up which will hamper the effectiveness of aca those of us who have insurance aren’t impacted by aca’s open enrollment period but there are millions of uninsured who absolutely do need health care who are depending on the obama administration delivering concerns will remain until stories from uninsured signing up and the numbers of those who getting insurance start shifting and actual numbers of those successfully enrolling are offered and confirmed by taylor marshoctober rd  comments share this story choose your platform facebooktwitterlinkedinreddittumblrgooglepinterestvkemail sort by   newest  oldest guestguyskishare on twittershare on google‘in what is a stunning admission secretary kathleen sebelius said that president obama didn’t know about the website problems before aca launched on october ’ no matter how this is interpretedtranslated it’s not really a stunning admission  years  months agoguestmjsmithshare on twittershare on googlei heard some people mention 